        "# Introduction to File Operations",
        "",
        "### **Opening a file**",
        "",
        "To open text or binary files, use the `OPENR`, `OPENU`, or `OPENW` functions.",
        "",
        "> Note: typing **?routine** into the IDL command line will take you to the documentation for a function or procedure. So **?OPENR** would open the OPENR documentation.",
        "",
        "For other types of files you can use any number of specialized reading/writing functions such as",
        "",
        "- `read_png`/`write_png`",
        "- `read_binary`",
        "- `read_csv`",
        "- `read_ascii`",
        "- **etc**",
        "",
        "These will take care of the `Open`for you.",
        ""
      ],
